  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The correct answer is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"880\"><mn>880</mn></math>. The volume, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper V\"><mi>V</mi></math>, of a right rectangular prism is given by the formula <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper V equals script l w h\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi><mi>w</mi><mi>h</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math> is the length, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"w\"><mi>w</mi></math> is the width, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h\"><mi>h</mi></math> is the height of the prism. It&rsquo;s given that a right rectangular prism has a length of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"11\"><mn>11</mn></math> meters, a width of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8\"><mn>8</mn></math> meters, and a height of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"10\"><mn>10</mn></math> meters. Substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"11\"><mn>11</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"script l\"><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8\"><mn>8</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"w\"><mi>w</mi></math>, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"10\"><mn>10</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h\"><mi>h</mi></math> in the formula <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper V equals script l w h\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"script\">l</mi><mi>w</mi><mi>h</mi></math> yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper V equals left parenthesis 11 right parenthesis left parenthesis 8 right parenthesis left parenthesis 10 right parenthesis\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"upper V equals 880\"><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>880</mn></math>. Therefore, the volume, in cubic meters, of the prism is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"880\"><mn>880</mn></math>.</p>",
